OL,3,CSon who cares for mum, 95, feels like
OL,4,C'second-class citizen' amid support
OL,5,Cworry
OL,7,FA son who cares for his 95-year-old
OL,8,Fmum in Rhondda Cynon Taf says they
OL,9,Ffeel like "second-class citizens" due
OL,10,Fto what he describes as a lack of
OL,11,Fsupport for unpaid carers in the area.
OL,13,FDavid Hiscox, of Treherbert, has cared
OL,14,Ffor his mother Peggy for 10 years, but
OL,15,Fin the last 18 months she has become
OL,16,Fbed-bound.
OL,18,FPeggy has dementia and Charles Bonnet
OL,19,FSyndrome, with carers visiting four
OL,20,Ftimes a day to dress and bathe her.
