OL,3,CSon who cares for mum, 95, feels like
OL,4,C'second-class citizen' amid support
OL,5,Cworry
OL,7,F"We had a discussion about it and I
OL,8,Fsaid to mum 'what would you like to
OL,9,Fhappen?' as she was advancing in years.
OL,11,F"She said 'I'd like you to look after
OL,12,Fme'. So, that was decided and we made
OL,13,Fthe move to come and live here in
OL,14,FTreherbert. I've looked after her on a
OL,15,F24/7 basis literally from then.
OL,17,F"Sometimes emotion does take over, but
OL,18,Fyou're doing a caring role and you
OL,19,Fhave to keep strong for that.
