OL,3,CSon who cares for mum, 95, feels like
OL,4,C'second-class citizen' amid support
OL,5,Cworry
OL,7,F"In a way I feel I'm failing my mother
OL,8,Fnot being able to help more, but I can
OL,9,Fonly do my best.
OL,11,F"We do feel up in the Rhondda that we
OL,12,Fare forgotten about up here. We wish
OL,13,Fthere could be more done.
OL,15,F"A lot of support groups have closed
OL,16,Fdown since Covid and not opened again."
OL,18,FHe added: "Day-to-day has its
OL,19,Fchallenges, with my own health not
OL,20,Fbeing brilliant.
